	<div class="ibox-image"><a href="./File:Chinese-grammar-wiki-wei.jpg" class="image"><img alt="Chinese-grammar-wiki-wei.jpg" src="https://resources.allsetlearning.com/gramwiki/images/thumb/3/33/Chinese-grammar-wiki-wei.jpg/300px-Chinese-grammar-wiki-wei.jpg" decoding="async" width="300" height="300" srcset="https://resources.allsetlearning.com/gramwiki/images/thumb/3/33/Chinese-grammar-wiki-wei.jpg/450px-Chinese-grammar-wiki-wei.jpg 1.5x, https://resources.allsetlearning.com/gramwiki/images/thumb/3/33/Chinese-grammar-wiki-wei.jpg/600px-Chinese-grammar-wiki-wei.jpg 2x" /></a></div>
</div> 
<p>为⋯⋯，而⋯⋯(wèi...ér...) is a structure used to clearly express the purpose of an action.
</p>
<div id="toc" class="toc"><input type="checkbox" role="button" id="toctogglecheckbox" class="toctogglecheckbox" style="display:none" /><div class="toctitle" lang="en" dir="ltr"><h2>Contents</h2><span class="toctogglespan"><label class="toctogglelabel" for="toctogglecheckbox"></label></span></div>
<ul>
<li class="toclevel-1 tocsection-1"><a href="ASG6509E#Structure"><span class="tocnumber">1</span> <span class="toctext">Structure</span></a></li>
<li class="toclevel-1 tocsection-2"><a href="ASG6509E#Examples"><span class="tocnumber">2</span> <span class="toctext">Examples</span></a></li>
<li class="toclevel-1 tocsection-3"><a href="ASG6509E#See_also"><span class="tocnumber">3</span> <span class="toctext">See also</span></a></li>
<li class="toclevel-1 tocsection-4"><a href="ASG6509E#Sources_and_further_reading"><span class="tocnumber">4</span> <span class="toctext">Sources and further reading</span></a>
<ul>
<li class="toclevel-2 tocsection-5"><a href="ASG6509E#Websites"><span class="tocnumber">4.1</span> <span class="toctext">Websites</span></a></li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
</div>

<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Structure">Structure</span></h2>
<div class="jiegou">
<p>Subj. + 为 + Goal + 而 + Efforts Made
</p>
</div>
<p>Sometimes, 为 can be replaced with <a href="为了" title="为了">为了</a>, which is less formal.
</p><p>To make the pattern negative, simply add 不 before 为:
</p>
<div class="jiegou">
<p>Subj. + 不 + 为 + Goal + 而 + Efforts Made
</p>
</div>
<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Examples">Examples</span></h2>
<div class="liju">
<ul><li>很多中国父母<em>为</em>孩子<em>而</em>活。<span class="pinyin">Hěnduō Zhōngguó fùmǔ <em>wèi</em> háizi <em>ér</em> huó.</span><span class="trans">Many Chinese parents live for their children.</span></li>
<li>我们<em>为</em>梦想<em>而</em>奋斗。<span class="pinyin">Wǒmen <em>wèi</em> mèngxiǎng <em>ér</em> fèndòu.</span><span class="trans">We fight for our dreams.</span></li>
<li><em>为</em>我们的健康<em>而</em>多做锻炼。<span class="pinyin"><em>Wèi</em> wǒmen de jiànkāng <em>ér</em> duō zuò duànliàn.</span><span class="trans">We exercise more for the sake of our health.</span></li>
<li>你是<em>为</em>钱<em>而</em>工作吗？<span class="pinyin">Nǐ shì <em>wèi</em> qián <em>ér</em> gōngzuò ma?</span><span class="trans">Do you work for money?</span></li>
<li>我是<em>为</em>朋友<em>而</em>做的这件事情。<span class="pinyin">Wǒ shì <em>wèi</em> péngyou <em>ér</em> zuò de zhè jiàn shìqing.</span><span class="trans">I'm doing this for a friend.</span></li>
<li>他<em>为了</em>能去日本<em>而</em>苦学日语。<span class="pinyin">Tā <em>wèile</em> néng qù Rìběn <em>ér</em> kǔxué Rìyǔ.</span><span class="trans">He studied Japanese hard in order to be able to go to Japan.</span></li>
<li>李甜<em>为了</em>男朋友<em>而</em>学的医生。<span class="pinyin">Lǐ Tián <em>wèile</em> nánpéngyou <em>ér</em> xué de yīshēng.</span><span class="trans">Li Tian studied to be a doctor for her boyfriend.</span></li>
<li>这不仅仅<em>是</em>为娱乐<em>而</em>修建的公园。<span class="pinyin">Zhè bùjǐn jǐn <em>shì</em> wèi yúlè <em>ér</em> xiūjiàn de gōngyuán.</span><span class="trans">This parks was not built solely for entertainment.</span></li>
<li>你<em>不为</em>父母<em>而</em>考虑，也要考虑考虑你自己。<span class="pinyin">Nǐ <em>bù wéi</em> fùmǔ <em>ér</em> kǎolǜ, yě yào kǎolǜ kǎolǜ nǐ zìjǐ.</span><span class="trans">You don't consider your parents, but consider yourself.</span></li>
<li><em>不为</em>明天<em>而</em>努力，那你为了什么而努力？<span class="pinyin"><em>Bù wéi</em> míngtiān <em>ér</em> nǔlì, nà nǐ wèile shénme ér nǔlì?</span><span class="trans">If you aren't working hard for tomorrow then what are you working so hard for?</span></li></ul>
</div>
